quran[59]{c,v,t}:
  44,1,M
  44,2,By the perspicuous Book
  44,3,"verily, we have sent it down on a blessed night;- verily, we had given warning"
  44,4,wherein is decided every wise affair
  44,5,"as an order from us. Verily, we were sending (apostles)"
  44,6,"a mercy from thy Lord; verily, He both hears and knows"
  44,7,"from the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what is between the two, if ye were but sure"
  44,8,"There is no god but He, He quickens and He kills - your Lord and the Lord of your fathers of yore"
  44,9,"Nay, they in doubt do play"
  44,10,But expect thou the day when the heaven shall bring obvious smoke
  44,11,to cover men - this is grievous torment
  44,12,"Our Lord! remove from us the torment; verily, we are believers"
  44,13,"How can they have the reminder (now), when they have had a plain apostle"
  44,14,"and when they turned their backs away from him and said, 'Taught! mad"
  44,15,"Verily, we will remove the torment a little, (but) ye will surely return"
  44,16,"On the day when we will assault with the great assault, verily, we will take vengeance"
  44,17,And we already tried the people of Pharaoh when there came to them a noble apostle
  44,18,"Send back to me God's servants; verily, I am to you a faithful apostle"
  44,19,"and, 'Exalt not yourselves above God; verily, I come to you with obvious authority"
  44,20,"And, verily, I seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord, that ye stone me not"
  44,21,And if ye believe not in me then let me alone
  44,22,"Then he called upon his Lord, 'Verily, these are a sinful people"
  44,23,"So journey with my servants by night - verily, ye will be pursued"
  44,24,"But leave the sea in quiet - verily, they are a host to be drowned"
  44,25,How many gardens and springs have they left
  44,26,and corn lands and a noble place
  44,27,and comfort wherein they did enjoy themselves
  44,28,Thus - and we gave them for an inheritance to another people
  44,29,"And the heaven wept not for them, nor the earth, nor were they respited"
  44,30,But we saved the children of Israel from shameful woe
  44,31,"from Pharaoh; verily, he was haughty, one of the extravagant"
  44,32,"And we did choose them, wittingly, above the worlds"
  44,33,and we gave them signs wherein was an obvious trial
  44,34,"Verily, these say"
  44,35,It is but our first death
  44,36,"so bring our fathers, if ye do speak the truth"
  44,37,"Are they better than the people of Tubbah, and those before them? We destroyed them - verily, they were sinners"
  44,38,"Nor did we create the heavens and the earth, and what is between the two in sport"
  44,39,"we did but create them in truth, though most of them know it not"
  44,40,"Verily, the day of separation is their appointed term"
  44,41,"the day when master shall not avail client at all, nor shall they be helped"
  44,42,"save whomsoever God shall have mercy on; verily, He is the mighty, the merciful"
  44,43,"Verily, the Zaqqum tree"
  44,44,(shall be) the food of the sinful
  44,45,"as it were melting, shall it boil in their bellies"
  44,46,like the boiling of hot water
  44,47,Take him and hale him into the midst of hell
  44,48,then pour over his head the torment of hot water
  44,49,"Taste! verily, thou art the mighty, the honourable"
  44,50,"Verily, this is that whereon ye did dispute"
  44,51,"Verily, the pious shall be in a safe place"
  44,52,in gardens and springs
  44,53,they shall be clad in satin and stout silk face to face
  44,54,Thus!- and we will wed them to bright and large-eyed maids
  44,55,They shall call therein for every fruit in safety
  44,56,"They shall not taste therein of death save their first death, and we will keep them from the torment of hell"
  44,57,"Grace from thy Lord, that is the grand bliss"
  44,58,"And we have only made it easy for thy tongue, that haply they may be mindful"
  44,59,"Then watch thou; verily, they are watching too"